perspective

This is a highlight reel of time with my family for which i am so grateful. It’s easy to see these images and think everything is perfect but that is very much not the case. And i want to take this caption to be clear about something…
I am highly aware of the pain this time of year brings for many people.

My heart breaks for those experiencing loss or who are alone for Christmas. Humanity is fragile. Life is hard and loss and disappointments can really beat a human heart up. I don’t have answers. I’ve struggled a lot this year mentally and that’s just me being real. 
But I do know the one thing I always come back to is my faith in Jesus. 
Talking to Him through the pain and disappointment. Laying it at His feet and asking Him to come through. When we create this posture of open, empty, helpless hands is when He can do His best work. 

I’m also a huge believer in the tools we have been given. If you are alone consider seeking out community. Join a church. Find people who you can be open with. 

If you’re struggling with your mental health take the initiative to seek help. Healing is a choice and there is so much color for us on the other side. 

Anyway if you took the time to read this far know that you’re not alone and the valley will not be forever 🤍
Breathe in His peace. He has you in the palm of His hand.

On the job priorities
 @nashvillerealtor_christen

This time last year I set a goal for 2022 to buy and furnish a home! 
It was the highlight of my year. As i was processing what my “big goal” for 2023 will be, I kept landing on the words “open hands.” 

I sat here starting the year in London truly having no idea what the next 12 months of my life will look like…and that’s OK. 

I’m giving God this year. Saying yes to the things He brings…And setting some micro goals on the meantime!! 

Here are a couple of them 

1. Morning routine: up at 7am coffee and time with the Lord to start my day

2. Lift weights, put on 10lbs of muscle 

3. Learn & expand somewhat into the commercial real estate space 

4. Start a Bible study 

5. Cook more

6. Close at least one deal a month 

7. Prioritize peace and mental health 

8. Be a better listener

9. Listen to one audible book a month 

10. Start a random acts of kindness foundation 

I’m starting here, I’m expectant. Bring it on 2023.

1. Contact a buyers agent. They are a FREE service at your disposal. Paid by the listing agent.

2. Your agent will help you obtain FINANCING & connect you with a bank to get pre-approved. 

3. Buyers agent will help you search for the perfect on or off-market property.

4. Negotiate an offer. If you go straight through a listing agent you must know they WORK FOR THE SELLER. Their primary due diligence is to the seller.

The more people I talk to the more I realize there is a lack of understanding on how working with a real estate agent actually works. A little EDUCATION on working with an agent:

Contrary to what some people think, you won’t save money by going straight through a listing agent. Contractually that commission will go to the listing company.

If you are wanting to purchase a home, there is no reason to try and do it on your own. A buyers agent is there to make the process as smooth and streamline as possible.

Haven’t done this in a hot minute, so wanted to just show up on here super real with y’all!

Unedited and fresh out of bed. Me on my couch. Where i have spent most of my week if I’m being honest lol. Feeling somewhat paralyzed trying to figure out direction for my life. 
Being hard on myself for not being further along in every area.

I come on this app and I post my workouts, my business, encouraging words, the fun I’m having, travels, my friends all these great and amazing things, and it gives the appearance that I’ve got it all together and am happy and unbothered at all times. 

But that’s just not reality. 

What y’all don’t see are weeks like this one. When i fight lies. Feel disappointed in myself. Face pain and frustration. All the humanity under the sun. 

The truth is, I am grateful for so much in my life. But you can be simultaneously grateful and struggle at the same time. 

So whatever your thing is this week, just want to say you’re not alone. And tomorrow is a new day and a fresh start. A blank slate! 

Give it to God. Sit down right now and set new goals for yourself. You’re not stuck. You’re never stuck.

Wishing you all a Holiday full of love and peace!! I recognize that this time of year can be especially hard if you are facing trials such as the sting of loss, financial hardship, loneliness, the list can go on…But just want to come on here and say i celebrate this day from a place of hope because of Jesus. 
Christmas symbolizes the day Jesus came into this world to bridge the gap between humanity and God. So no matter how hopeless the Holidays may have felt this year, He offers us the hope of eternal life lived in total wholeness, and unity with our loved ones. He knocks on the door of every humans heart and all we have to do is let Him in. Let Him love on you this year. Merry Christmas to my internet friends ♥️
